        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-slate-900">Is density the same as weight?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">No. Density is weight per volume. Two ingredients can weigh the same per tablespoon but have different densities per cup if they pack differently.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 p-3">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-slate-900">Can I treat all liquids as 1 g/mL?</summary>
        <p class="mt-2 text-slate-700">Only if you want approximations. Oils and syrups deviate significantly from water, so use their specific densities for accurate baking.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
